---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const updated = "March 25th 2025";
---

<BaseLayout brand="marysse" title="Cookie Policy">
  <section class="legal-page">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      This Cookie Policy explains how cookies and similar technologies are used on
      <strong>www.maryssedesign.com</strong>.
      Cookies help improve website functionality, performance and user experience.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website.
      They allow the website to recognise your device and remember certain information
      about your preferences or actions over time.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Types of Cookies Used</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Essential cookies</strong><br />
        Required for the correct functioning of the website and cannot be disabled.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics cookies</strong><br />
        Used to collect aggregated and anonymised information about website usage
        (e.g. Google Analytics).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Functional cookies</strong><br />
        Allow the website to remember user preferences and improve functionality.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Marketing / Affiliate cookies</strong><br />
        Used to track referrals and interactions with affiliate links, including
        those related to the Amazon Associates Program.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Amazon Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      This website participates in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program.
      As an Amazon Associate, Marysse may earn a commission from qualifying purchases
      made through affiliate links. These cookies do not increase the price paid by users.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Some cookies are set by third-party services used on this website,
      such as analytics or embedded content providers. These third parties
      are responsible for their own cookies and privacy practices.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Managing Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Users can manage or disable cookies directly through their browser settings.
      Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect website functionality
      and user experience.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This Cookie Policy may be updated from time to time.
      Users are encouraged to review this page periodically to stay informed
      about how cookies are used.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Contact Information</h2>
    <p>
      For any questions regarding this Cookie Policy, you may contact:
      <a href="mailto:info@maryssedesign.com">info@maryssedesign.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
